is slower than in C. crispus. A reduced surface area:biomass
ratio coupled with greater strength may lessen wave-induced
disturbance and be important to maintaining a high abundance of
M. stellatus in the low intertidal zone of wave-swept shores. {\textcopyright}
1993.},
