stipe internodes to mature. Deduced relative growth rates in
stipe tissue and pneumatocyst fresh weight decreased from 0.24
(loge units per day) at the apex to 0.11 at 200 mm, where basal
lamina tissue had a rate of 0.29, a doubling in just over 2 d.
The production of tissue per frond was estimated as 25 and 36 g
fresh wt d-1 at Aquarium Point and in California, respectively.},
